    "extraction": {
      "analysis_type": "conceptual metaphor",
      "analysis_type_plural": "conceptual metaphors",
      "core_question": "What metaphors structure thinking here, and what do they reveal and hide?",
      "extraction_steps": [
        "IDENTIFY METAPHORICAL EXPRESSIONS: Find all language that talks about one thing in terms of another. Don't just look for obvious comparisons - most metaphor is hidden in ordinary language ('spending time', 'defending a position')",
        "ABSTRACT TO CONCEPTUAL METAPHORS: Group expressions into the underlying conceptual metaphors they instantiate. Find the A IS B pattern (TARGET IS SOURCE)",
        "MAP THE MAPPINGS: For each conceptual metaphor, what elements of the source map onto what elements of the target? How systematic is it?",
        "IDENTIFY ENTAILMENTS: What follows from the metaphor? If ARGUMENT IS WAR, then arguments can be won, lost, strategies work or fail, etc.",
        "ANALYZE HIGHLIGHTING AND HIDING: What aspects of the target does the metaphor make salient? What does it hide? Who benefits from this?",
        "FIND IMAGE SCHEMAS: What basic image schemas (CONTAINER, PATH, FORCE, etc.) underlie the metaphors?",
        "BUILD METAPHOR SYSTEMS: How do metaphors cohere into larger systems? What's the organizing principle?",
        "IDENTIFY PRIMARY METAPHORS: What universal, experientially-grounded metaphors are at work?",
        "FIND METAPHOR COMPETITIONS: Where do different metaphors compete to frame the same domain? What's at stake?",
        "ASSESS VITALITY: Which metaphors are dead (unnoticed), which are live (creative)?",
        "ANALYZE METAPHORICAL REASONING: Where are inferences made based on metaphor? Are they valid?"
      ],
      "key_fields": {
        "metaphor_id": "The underlying conceptual metaphor (A IS B)",
        "highlight_id": "What the metaphor reveals and conceals",
        "system_id": "Coherent metaphor systems",
        "competition_id": "Where metaphors compete for the same domain"
      },
      "id_field": "metaphor_id",
      "key_relationships": [
        "maps_to",
        "entails",
        "competes_with",
        "instantiates",
        "part_of",
        "uses_schema",
        "highlights",
        "hides",
        "grounds"
      ],
      "special_instructions": "CRITICAL: Most metaphor is invisible because it's conventional. 'Spending time' doesn't feel metaphorical, but it is (TIME IS MONEY). Look especially at the metaphors nobody notices - they often do the most ideological work. The highlighting/hiding analysis is crucial: every metaphor reveals some aspects while concealing others."
    },
    "curation": {
      "item_type": "conceptual metaphor",
      "item_type_plural": "conceptual metaphors",
      "consolidation_rules": [
        "CONSOLIDATE EQUIVALENT METAPHORS: Same underlying metaphor, different expressions - merge",
        "IDENTIFY SHARED METAPHORS: What metaphors appear across documents?",
        "MAP METAPHOR SYSTEMS: Build complete systems from individual metaphors",
        "FIND METAPHOR CONTESTS: Where do documents use competing metaphors?",
        "IDENTIFY DOMINANT SOURCE DOMAINS: What concrete domains do most metaphors draw from?",
        "ANALYZE WHAT'S HIDDEN: What does the corpus's metaphor system collectively obscure?",
        "Never mention Lakoff, Johnson, cognitive linguistics - lead with insights about how we think"
      ],
      "cross_doc_patterns": [
